\nAlso, I want to verify if there\'s any `auth.yaml` OpenAPI contract and if the
generated types actually reference it properly. Let me check the auth.yaml file.
\n\nActually, let me think about what I\'ve found so far and compile the review:
\n\n**Major Issues:**\n1. **Auth module missing**: The PRD requires age validati
on during registration (blocking underage users with code 1000). The `calculateA
ge` utility exists with good tests, but there\'s no `AuthModule` in `apps/api/sr
c/modules/` and it\'s not wired into `AppModule`. This means the age calculator 
is orphaned and the critical compliance feature is not implemented.\n2. **Mobile
Sentry missing**: PRD/execution plan requires `sentry_flutter` initialization in
`apps/mobile/lib/main.dart`. The file is completely bare - no Sentry, no error t
racking.\n3. **Mobile pubspec missing shared-types dependency**: The PRD require
s `packages/shared-types` to resolve as a local path dependency in mobile, but `
apps/mobile/pubspec.yaml` only references `social_world_design_system`, not `soc
ial_world_shared_types` or the generated auth models.\n4. **Admin Dashboard is m
ock data**: The dashboard page shows hardcoded user list instead of calling `GET
